Bojan's clutch shot (yes, it was very clutch and I'm saying this as a Houston fan and even better for him as he wasn't even good throughout the game)

Harden's inconsistent (he's actually not just the threes are making his FG% look eh and he was missing makeable FTs)

Westbrook "carried" Houston (Relax😂 he was great but relax)

Clarkson was great (great for my Fantasy lol)

Someone said Bojan ended Harden's career on this shot and I want to say this. No he didn't.

No one will talk about how Houston played absolutely well vs the Jazz. If anything, they won today's game (not literally).

Great game but let's not forget Houston will still beat this team playoffs team if this game show any indication (also, the Bojan shot will most likely not happen again during playoffs time)

Also, I'm not trying to seem like I'm hating or anything just expressing my opinions on the comments as no one is actually saying things that matter outside of the last 40 seconds lol
